Class ExpressionQuant

  • java.lang.Object
    • parser.ast.ASTElement
      • parser.ast.Expression
        • parser.ast.ExpressionQuant
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExpressionProb, ExpressionReward, ExpressionSS

    public abstract class ExpressionQuant
extends Expression
    Abstract class for representing "quantitative" operators (P,R,S), i.e., a superclass of ExpressionProb, ExpressionReward, ExpressionSS.

    • Field Detail

      • modifier

        protected java.lang.String modifier
        Optional "modifier" to specify variants of the P/R/S operator

      • relOp

        protected RelOp relOp
        The attached relational operator (e.g. "<" in "P<0.1").

      • bound

        protected Expression bound
        The attached (probability/reward) bound, as an expression (e.g. "p" in "P<p"). Null if absent (e.g. "P=?").

      • expression

        protected Expression expression
        The main operand of the operator (e.g. "F target=true" in "P<0.1[F target=true].

      • filter

        protected Filter filter
        Optional "old-style" filter. This is just for display purposes since the parser creates an (invisible) new-style filter around this expression.

      • getRelopBoundInfo

        public abstract OpRelOpBound getRelopBoundInfo(Values constantValues)
                                        throws PrismException
        Get an object storing info about the attached relational operator and bound, after evaluating the bound to a double. For example "<0.1" in "P<p" where p=0.5 in constantValues. Does some checks, e.g., throws an exception if a probability is not in the range [0,1]
        Parameters:
        constantValues - Values for constants in order to evaluate any bound
        Throws:
        PrismException
